SIMPLE: austerity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Austerity
<hw>Aus*ter"i*ty</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Austerities</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F.
<ets>aust⟦eacute⟧rit⟦eacute⟧</ets>, L. <ets>austerias</ets>, fr.
<ets>austerus</ets>. See <er>Austere</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Sourness and harshness to the taste.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Horsley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Severity of manners or life; extreme rigor or
strictness; harsh discipline.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>austerity</qex> of John the Baptist.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Plainness; freedom from adornment; severe
simplicity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Partly owing to the studied <qex>austerity</qex> of her dress, and
partly to the lack of demonstration in her manners.</q>
<rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Austerlitz</ent>⟦br⟧
